"google.com") that points to an IP address and helps users to access websites or other resources in a convenient way. ==Extensions== See main article: URL Domain names have extensions (called "top-level domains") at the end of the URL. For example ".com", ".net" and ".org" are the most commonly used domain name extensions. The most popular domain extension is .com with more than 100 million domains registered. The .com extension stands for "commercial", .org for organization and .net for network. There are also country-specific domain name extensions. For example, the United Kingdom has the ".uk" domain extension and Japan has ".jp". ==Related pages== *Domain Name System *Domain name registrar ==References==
